\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af1\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af1\langfe2052\hich\f1\fs24\lang2057\loch\f1\fs24\lang2057 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f8\fs24\lang2057\i\b0 This report, to be delivered to the committee this Spring First in the Year That Crocus Blossomed For The First Time Amongst The Brubbage Ribs, must make clear that the man such as this John Caboot, who even now is installed patiently, I must confess, on o
ur borders, must be requested to leave peacefully. He poses a danger to our health, our way of life and the base sanctity of our community. I must respectfully impeach that he is removed at the earliest opportunity.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af1\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af1\langfe2052\hich\f1\fs24\lang2057\loch\f1\fs24\lang2057 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f8\fs24\lang2057\i\b0 I was amongst those that witnessed this man ride down into the valley along with one of the woodcutters. His appearance, to say the least, was frightening and unwelcoming; a long vestment, high peasant sandals for riding, his haversack stuffed full with da
ngerous shapes, a strange wooden augur at his side clutched in one gloved hand, and a ghoulish mask on his face, with glass over his eyes and a long trunk where his mouth should be. Such an individual, with such evident malice, could not enter our lives as
 a friend. His visage is an invite to war.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af1\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af1\langfe2052\hich\f8\fs24\lang2057\loch\f8\fs24\lang2057{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f8\fs24\lang2057\i0\b0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\i\loch\i Though the man has abided by our wishes to remain outside the town gates until this report is published, he has shown little respect for any of our other purities. He constantly coquettes with the girls that come to watch him by the gateposts, but ignores 
the boys that follow them; he has often thrown them scraps of paper with mysterious passages scrawled on them, strange food from outside the valley, and trinkets and baubles that he pulls from his pack. My own daughter will rarely come home before midnigh
t, entranced by this exotic wight who claims to have crossed the dark sea. I propose that his presence will only provoke a dangerous ambition within our young, to our detriment; the outside world is a tempting lure for the stupid.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1081\ai\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe2052\hich\f8\fs24\lang2057\i\loch\f8\fs24\lang2057\i {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f8\fs24\lang2057\i\b0 How this man found his route here is a completely separate matter; when quizzed by myself earlier on in the week, he stated that he had come \'81\'67writing in the saddle, pouring drink to us, ready to drink with us, to work demons with us.\'81\'68 Even if such an odd s
tatement were true (which we have no way of verifying) the thought of a fugitive conjurer (or whatever his provenance must be) cataloguing our way of life is complete anathema to what this civil thane believes this town stands for. I have asked him for cre
dentials, and he has only given me scraps of paper with strange symbols and ranked lines upon them, more spells and problems for a town with enough of its own. }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af1\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af1\langfe2052\hich\f1\fs24\lang2057\loch\f1\fs24\lang2057 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f8\fs24\lang2057\i\b0 If these uncertainties and dangers were not enough to warrant this man's ejection from our community, I would like to draw the committee's attention to the Hidden Press, in its wisdom, and I know that I draw no friends with this tactic. Though the word of 
the Press is no longer writ by law, its teachings still hold some value for this humble servant, and will, hopefully, have some bearing on the committee's decision. I speak only for Whisper, and his eternal absence. His wisdom still moves me. Let it move y
ou. }
