\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe2052\hich\f8\fs24\lang2057\loch\f8\fs24\lang2057 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f8\fs24\lang2057\i0\b0 \tab Coming downstairs on my second day I met two serious young men racing out of the main door to the apartment block. One was slighter, paler than the other, and his soul seemed to know that it was sickly; he is not seen to smile. The other is heavier set, a
nd tanned; he obviously spends more time outdoors. Maybe the first one is a writer, I remember thinking. As I engaged them with a rap of my book against the wall they scratched to a stop, shuffled nervously, and introduced themselves as Discovering Leprosy
 and Love For All Gods, and I realised that I had taken photographs of them on my first day here; I met so many people I had quite forgotten about them. They said that they were sportsmen, though Discovering Leprosy gave Love For All Gods a sharp look when
