s cobbled here, the grass spongey and lush in that way that points to frequent digging. The graveyard is a deep hollow cut into the valley floor many years before, and part of the mountain that rears above it. How the townspeople made such a depression wit
hout heavy machinery is beyond me; but I am learning not to question everything that I see here. I have plenty of time to find where they keep the trebuchets and cranes. }
