. When I then me
rely deigned to ask them what they were singing, they began laughing and slapping me about the back and shoulders, while I tried to help them! I immediately dropped my corner of the screen and left to recline under a nearby willow.  One of them came to joi
n me, ruffled my hair and grimly stamped on a large beetle, a Pageant Weevil and full of deadly venom. He picked a small fern (see below)  that he told me would help if I ever was stung. I asked if it was to be ingested or used as a poultice, and he told m
